 journalism to its manipulation. One positive consequence of these practices has been to invigorate television journalists' unique brand of advocacy journalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aChina-Politics and government-2002-. 0aInvestigative reporting-Political aspects-China. 0aLocal mass media-Political aspects-China. 0aPress and politics-China. 0aTelevision broadcasting of news-Political aspects-China. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Studies. 4aAsian Studies : Chinese Studies. 4aCommunication : Political Communication. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Mass Media. 4aSociology : Urban Sociology. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / Local.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2020z978311149149340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848031240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438480312423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438480312/original  a978-3-11-149149-3  SUNY Press eBook Package 2020b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles